We can use polynomial long division to divide $6x^4-14x^3-4x^2+2x-26$ by $2x - 6$.
\[
\begin{array}{c|ccccc}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{3x^3 - 4x^2 - x + 1} \\
\cline{2-6}
2x - 6 & 6x^4 - 14x^3 - 4x^2 + 2x - 26 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{- (6x^4 - 18x^3)} \\
\cline{2-3}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{4x^3 - 4x^2} \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{- (4x^3 - 12x^2)} \\
\cline{2-3}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{8x^2 + 2x} \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{- (8x^2 - 24x)} \\
\cline{2-3}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{26x - 26} \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{- (26x - 78)} \\
\cline{2-3}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{52} \\
\end{array}
\]
Therefore, the remainder is $\boxed{52}$.The answer is: 52

